'''大历史'''（Big History）是一个新興學術領域，探索从[[大爆炸|宇宙大爆炸]]到現代的[[歷史|歷史]]。它通過包括[[科學|科學]]、[[人文|人文]]等多種學科的跨學科方法來檢視長遠的[[时间|时间框架]]，<ref name="tws2M27">{{Cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/rev-michael-dowd/big-news-about-big-histor_b_1477137.html|title=Big History Hits the Big Time|date=May 8, 2012|work=Huffington Post|accessdate=2012-12-13|quote="Big History" has entered the big leagues ...|author=Rev. Michael Dowd|archive-date=2017-04-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170430081752/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/rev-michael-dowd/big-news-about-big-histor_b_1477137.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="tws2M13">{{Cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/27/arts/deep-history-takes-humanity-back-to-its-origins.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0|title=History That's Written in Beads as Well as in Words|date=September 26, 2011|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2012-12-13|author=Patricia cohen|archive-date=2013-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130602151103/http://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/27/arts/deep-history-takes-humanity-back-to-its-origins.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="tws2M12">{{Cite news|url=http://www.npr.org/blogs/13.7/2011/02/10/133652898/its-time-for-a-new-narrative-its-time-for-big-history|title=It's Time for a New Narrative; It's Time for 'Big History'|date=February 10, 2011|work=[[NPR|NPR]]|accessdate=2012-12-13|author=Ursula Goodenough|archive-date=2012-05-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120523144613/http://www.npr.org/blogs/13.7/2011/02/10/133652898/its-time-for-a-new-narrative-its-time-for-big-history|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="tws2M31">Tom Vander Ark (December 13, 2012). </ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Maps of Time: An Introduction to Big History|year=2004|url=https://archive.org/details/mapsoftimeintrod00chri|last=Christian|first=David}}</ref> 并在更大的背景之下探讨人类存在的意義。<ref name="PeterStearns">{{Cite book|title=Growing Up: The History of Childhood in a Global Context|last=Stearns|first=Peter N.|page=9}}</ref> 它整合宇宙、地球、生命和人类的研究，使用经验，证据来探索[[因果关系|因果]]关系，<ref name="tws2M11">{{Cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/education/2012/oct/28/big-history-bill-gates-david-christian|title=Big History theories pose latest challenge to traditional curriculum: Maverick academic's 'Big History' – which is backed by Bill Gates – is subject of new documentary|date=27 October 2012|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|accessdate=2012-12-13|quote=Big History, a movement spearheaded by the [[University_of_Oxford|Oxford]]-educated maverick historian David Christian,...|author=Vanessa Thorpe|archive-date=2012-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121119011552/http://www.guardian.co.uk/education/2012/oct/28/big-history-bill-gates-david-christian|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="IBHA">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ibhanet.org/|title=International Big History Association|accessdate=September 17, 2012|archive-date=2018-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120074214/http://www.ibhanet.org/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 它被講授於大学<ref name="tws2M42">{{Cite news |url=http://www.hssonline.org/publications/Newsletter2012/July-big-history.html |title=Recent Developments in Big History |date=July 2012 |work=[[History_of_Science_Society|History of Science Society]] |authorlink=Craig Benjamin |accessdate=2012-12-13 |quote=Vol. 41, No. 3, |author=Craig Benjamin |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130109012654/http://www.hssonline.org/publications/Newsletter2012/July-big-history.html |archivedate=2013-01-09 }}</ref> 和中学<ref name="tws2M16">{{Cite news|url=http://www.boston.com/2012/10/05/bigideas/SbrOrY1bEXcOZU0rDMLCGP/story.html|title=5 big ideas that just might transform the classroom: From longer days to history courses that span 13.7 billion years, these notions just might transform the classroom.|work=[[Boston_Globe_Magazine|Boston Globe Magazine]]|accessdate=2012-12-13|year=2012|quote=1. TAKE THE REALLY LONG VIEW|author=Stephanie M. McPherson|archive-date=2016-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009053826/http://archive.boston.com/2012/10/05/bigideas/SbrOrY1bEXcOZU0rDMLCGP/story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 經常使用基于网路的互動式专题來介绍。<ref name="tws2M16"/> 此运动涉及澳大利亚[[麦考瑞大学|麦考瑞大学]]之历史学家{{le|大卫·克利斯汀|David Christian (historian)}}，他创造了「大的历史」这个词，<ref name="tws2M11"/><ref name="tws2M42"/><ref name="tws2M32">{{Cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/rev-michael-dowd/failing-our-youth-a-call-to-religious-liberals_b_2267640.html|title=Failing Our Youth: A Call to Religious Liberals|date=December 13, 2012|work=[[Huffington_Post|Huffington Post]]|accessdate=2012-12-13|quote=Historian David Christian ... "big history."|author=Connie Barlow and Michael Dowd|archive-date=2017-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325010913/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/rev-michael-dowd/failing-our-youth-a-call-to-religious-liberals_b_2267640.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 并且是由一个「学者的不寻常联盟」所成就。<ref name="tws2M13"/>

一个「大历史」的早期例子发现於[[约翰·肯尼迪|约翰·肯尼迪]]在[[萊斯大學|萊斯大學]]的着名演讲，他將50,000年的人类历史濃縮為半个世纪來講解。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WZyRbnpGyzQ&t=1m58s |title=JFK speech at Rice (video) |accessdate=2016-07-08 |archive-date=2016-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160317040712/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WZyRbnpGyzQ&t=1m58s |dead-url=no }}</ref> 一些历史学家表示对「[[史前時代|科学历史]]」表示怀疑，并认为「大历史」之宣稱沒有独创性。<ref name="tws2M19">{{Cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/science/the-h-word/2012/aug/16/history-science|title=(Pseudo)scientific history?: At least one historical prediction holds true: the regular appearance of claims to have the key to 'scientific history'|date=16 August 2012|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|accessdate=2012-12-13|quote=... Peter Turchin ... to explain 'big history' – things like the rise of empires, social discontent, civil wars, and state collapse". ...|author=Rebekah Higgitt|archive-date=2013-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130222182835/http://www.guardian.co.uk/science/the-h-word/2012/aug/16/history-science|dead-url=no}}</ref>

